"v.死，暴卒 【英】 v. 死，暴卒(to become destroyed or ruined; die) 【考】 反义词:survive(生存 ) 【例】 Fourteen people perished in the hotel fire. / perish from disease(病死) v. (在暴力下或以突然的方式)死; 渐渐消失 【记】pe破, rish读: 瑞士－瑞士是生活的地方, 但破瑞士就不一样了, 是死人的地方. 【参】perishable(adj 容易腐烂的); perishing(adj 冻死人的; 可憎的) 【反】survive(v 幸存; 生还) 【记】peril 危险 + sh(音：死)，危险，然后死；音：抛肉尸，抛尸荒野；音：皮肉死 perish (v.)  mid-13c., from periss- present participle stem of Old French perir ""perish, be lost, be shipwrecked"" (12c.), from Latin perire ""to be lost, perish,"" literally ""to go through,"" from per- ""through, completely, to destruction"" (see per) + ire ""to go"" (see ion). Related: Perished; perishing."
